{{Short description|Location in Shinto mythology}} {{Draft topics|philosophy-and-religion|east-asia}} {{AfC topic|other}}
<!-- Note: The following pages were redirects to [[Everlasting_world]] before draftification: *[[Tokoyo Yomi]] *[[Draft:Tokoyo]] *[[Draft:Everlasting world 2]] *[[Tokoyo and Kakuriyo]] *[[Draft:Everlasting 2]] *[[Tokoyo (eternal night)]] *[[Unseen world]] *[[Draft:Tokoyo Yomi]] *[[Draft:Tokoyo and Kakuriyo]] *[[Draft:Tokoyo (eternal night)]] --> {{refimprove|date=December 2022}}
{{nihongo|Tokoyo|常世|}}.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web |title=Encyclopedia of Shinto詳細 |url=https://d-museum.kokugakuin.ac.jp/eos/detail/?id=8740 |access-date=2023-03-10 |website=國學院大學デジタルミュージアム |language=ja}}</ref>, also known as {{nihongo|Unseen world|隠世、幽世|Kakuriyo}},<ref name=":1">{{Cite web |title=隠り世(かくりよ)と現世（うつしよ）、隠り世ってどんなところ？ - waqwaq |url=https://waqwaq-j.com/japan/1093/ |access-date=2022-12-22 |website=waqwaq-j.com}}</ref> or Taikaikan<ref>{{Cite web |date=2018-02-19 |title=國學院デジタルミュージアム |url=http://web.archive.org/web/20180219090216/http://k-amc.kokugakuin.ac.jp/DM/detail.do?class_name=col_eos&data_id=23640 |access-date=2023-03-10 |website=web.archive.org}}</ref> is a world in [[shinto]] which never changes<ref name=":1" />
In this world people have [[eternal youth]].<ref name=":4" /> There arew two main related terms
== Hidden World == "Kakuriyo" or "Yuusei" (also translated as "hidden world") is believed to be the afterlife. It is often contrasted with the present world, known as "[[Utsushiyo]]" or "[[Gense]]", and is thought to be a a world where dead ancestors and friends reside<ref name=":1" />.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |url=https://archive.ph/wip/9hRmR |access-date=2022-12-22 |website=archive.ph}}</ref> The "Yuusei" is not in stark opposition to the "Utsushiyo", but rather exists in parallel to it, and it is suggested that it is a place where ancestors, friends, and loved ones who have passed away reside.<ref name=":0" />
"Yuusei" is believed to have stronger connotations of the "Tokoyo" as a paradise, or "ideal world". The kanji for "Yuusei" can also be written as "Kakuriyo" and can also be translated as "hidden world". The "Yuusei" is not in stark opposition to the "Utsushiyo", but rather exists in parallel to it, and it is suggested that it is a place where ancestors, friends, and loved ones who have passed away reside.<ref name=":0" />
== Tokoyo == In contrast to Kakuriyo {{nihongo|2=常世|3={{ill|Unseen world|lt=Tokoyo|ja|常世}}}} is a similar concept often associated with negative connotations such as hell or the land of the dead.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=常世 (とこよ) - さくら葬祭 |url=https://sakurasousai.jp/dict_info/ta-007/#:~:text=%E5%B8%B8%E4%B8%96%EF%BC%88%E3%81%A8%E3%81%93%E3%82%88%EF%BC%89%E3%81%A8%E3%81%AF,%E5%B8%B8%E5%A4%9C%E3%80%8D%E3%81%A8%E3%82%82%E8%A1%A8%E8%A8%98%E3%81%97%E3%81%9F%E3%80%82 |access-date=2022-12-22 |website=sakurasousai.jp}}</ref> Tokoyo' is a world which is always in the dead of the night,<ref name=":3">{{Cite web |title=隠世（かくりよ） - 零 濡鴉の巫女 |url=https://sites.google.com/site/zeronurekarasu/yong-yu/yin-shi-kakuriyo |access-date=2022-12-22 |website=sites.google.com}}</ref> and it is sometimes identified with the world of the dead and yominokuni (realm of the dead) from the meaning of the [[kanji]] of tokoyo (常夜).<ref>{{Cite web |last=日本国語大辞典 |first=精選版 |title=隠世とは |url=https://kotobank.jp/word/%E9%9A%A0%E4%B8%96-2021028 |access-date=2022-12-22 |website=コトバンク |language=ja}}</ref>
In ancient Shinto and Japanese texts, "Tokoyo" is described as a place located beyond mountains, seas, forests, rivers, and giant rocks. It is often described as a place where the god Sukuna-biko-no-kami, who helped create the country, goes after completing his mission. In addition, it is said that this world is connected to different spaces through the boundaries of different landscapes such as deep sea, mountain<ref name=":2" /> == See also ==
* [[This world]] * [[Yorishiro]] * [[Shimenawa]] * [[Bai sema]] * [[Otherworld]] * [[Amatsukami and Kunitsukami]]
