{{AFC comment|1=I think the current content is good at explaining about the world, but before being accepted the article would probably benefit from a bit more discussion about the context for people unfamiliar with Shinto. You could maybe also expand on some of the discussion about it in certain tales, similar to the article on [[Asgard]]. I'd also suggest using a few different sources throughout the article, as although you've cited half a dozen or so it seems that the bulk of the article is linked to a single source. [[User:Turnagra|Turnagra]] ([[User talk:Turnagra|talk]]) 09:49, 3 June 2023 (UTC)}}
{{AFC comment|1={{Ping|Robert McClenon}} Not only do I think that is not the primary usage, but actually most links and references to the title on wikipedia were referencing this, or misspellings of [[Tokyo]], and that page was rather obscure. I moved the page to [[Tokoyo (fictional character)]] and changed the few links actually intending that character to that, and redirected the page to something more fitting for the time being[[User:Immanuelle|'''Immanuel'''le]] ❤️💚💙 [[User_talk:Immanuelle|(talk to the cutest Wikipedian)]] 16:24, 12 March 2023 (UTC)}}
